{"build_type":"library","description":"Build-time self-description injection for one tool artifact, matched to the disk-path-based compiler (closure AND closure-expansion read source from disk by path). Steps: locate the tool's universe entry by package name; derive its contract from the CLEAN parsed doc; inject the describe prologue into the in-memory entry; serialize the now-injected doc and WRITE it to a generation-scoped <name>.injected.ipm under gen_bin_dir (never touching the original source); repoint the universe entry's path valuestring to the injected file (so find_target_and_seed records the injected path); AND repoint the index entry for the entry function to the injected path (so gx_one_package, which re-reads disk during closure expansion, scans the injected source and pulls emit_contract_text_if_describe_requested + its deps into the closure). Without the index repoint the injected call is unresolved -> segfault. Caller gates which artifacts get this. Reuses find_entry_by_package_name_loop1, locate_named_member_inside_mapping, derive_tool_contract_from_package_doc, render_document_value_producing_cstring, inject_describe_prologue_into_instructions, create_empty_string_buffer, append_cstring_into_string_buffer, build_store_path, open_file_for_writing, compute_string_length_by_scanning, write_bytes_to_file, close_open_file, field_write.","module_name":"materialize-injected-helper-source-instructions","package_name":"materialize-injected-helper-source-instructions","function_definitions":{"materialize-injected-helper-source-instructions":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"art","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"universe","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"gen_bin_dir","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"index","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"ins